creator: sakthi.sensational@gmail.com
text:
Hello,

An error occurred in version 2.4.26 while rpmbuild, for the fix in this mod_proxy_hcheck.so (version 2.4.26).


Checking for unpackaged file(s): /usr/lib/rpm/check-files /root/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/httpd-2.4.26-1.x86_64
error: Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found:
   /usr/lib64/httpd/modules/mod_proxy_hcheck.so


RPM build errors:
    Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found:
   /usr/lib64/httpd/modules/mod_proxy_hcheck.so

I found the same error in this Bug ID 60506. In the previous version 2.4.25, add this line into httpd.spec, it will pass:

%{_libdir}/httpd/modules/mod_proxy_hcheck.so

But 2.4.26 add the above line into httpd.spec, not passing

Will follow up there.

*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 60506 ***
